      "lesson title": "AI and Seasonal Variability",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "Seasonal changes can have a surprising impact on how AI systems perform, and understanding why this happens is an important first step for anyone working with AI tools. This lesson explores how AI models are trained on historical data, and why that data may not always reflect the conditions the model encounters in the real world. When seasons shift, consumer behaviour, environmental patterns, and operational demands can all change significantly, leaving an AI system struggling to keep up. We will look at practical examples of where this mismatch can cause problems, from retail forecasting to energy management, and consider what can be done to reduce the risk. By the end of this lesson, you will have a clearer understanding of why seasonal variability matters and how to approach it with greater confidence.",
