          "slidecontent": "• Retraining models on recent seasonal data before peak periods begin\n• Scheduling regular model reviews tied to known calendar shifts\n• Short retraining cycles beat annual updates\n• Flagging known high-variability windows (holidays, harvests, weather events) in advance\n• Building in human oversight during transition periods to catch early drift\n• Small, frequent adjustments rather than large, infrequent overhauls"
