          "subtitle": "Core lessons to carry forward",
          "slidecontent": "• AI systems trained on one season's data often struggle when conditions shift unexpectedly\n• Seasonal change is a common, real-world trigger for model failure\n• Patterns learned in summer may be completely wrong by winter\n• Always question whether your AI tool was trained on data that matches your current context\n• Small shifts in conditions can compound into large, costly errors over time\n• A good next step is to ask your AI provider how often their models are retrained and on what data"
